# Swift style (NoteStream)

Follow a standard-library / Google Swift Style aligned style:

- **UTF-8 only**, spaces for indentation (no tabs).
- **No semicolons**.
- **One statement per line** (except allowed single-statement blocks).
- **K&R braces** (`} else {` on one line).
- **No horizontal alignment** with extra spaces (avoid “tabular” alignment in code).
- **Avoid force unwrap/cast** in production code (allowed in tests when appropriate).
- **Prefer shorthand types** (`[T]`, `[K: V]`, `T?`) when possible.
- **Guard for early exits**; keep main logic less-indented.
- **Keep lines ≤ 100 columns** unless it would harm readability (e.g., long URLs).
- **Imports are explicit and minimal** (don’t rely on transitive imports).

When adding new Swift files, prefer naming by primary type:

- `TypeName.swift`
- `TypeName+Protocol.swift` for protocol-conformance extensions

